iam Bascom, Jan de Vries, G. S. Kirk, James G. Frazer, Theodor H. Gaster, Mircea Eliade, Bronislaw Malinowski, C. G. Jung, and Claude Lévi-Strauss.Rather than limiting this collection to classical Roman and Greek mythology, Dundes gives the book a worldwide scope. The twenty-two essays by leading experts on myth represent comparative functionalist, myth-ritual, Jungian, Freudian, and structuralist approaches to studying the genre.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAncient & Classical. 4aLiterary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aBaaren, Th. P. van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBascom, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDardel, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDundes, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDundes, Alan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEliade, Mircea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdesz, Sändor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFirth, Raymond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrazer, James G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaster, Theodor H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonko, Lauri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHultkrantz, Ake, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJung, C. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirk, G. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLévi-Strauss, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb